That can be misleading because it obscures differences between provinces with very different high counts (Ontario vs Quebec). However, since the map also includes data labels with exact numbers, the viewer can see the differences. But typical choropleth design uses categories; here the highest category is open-ended, which can be considered a design choice but not necessarily misleading.
